ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa says the ANC national executive committee (NEC) has instructed suspended secretary-general Ace Magashule to apologise publicly to ANC structures for the suspension letter Magashule addressed to Ramaphosa last week. Ramaphosa said the NEC noted that Magashule no power or mandate from the party’s highest decision-making body to pen such a letter. Ramaphosa also made it clear that Magashule remains suspended from the party while his corruption case is being heard in court. Ramaphosa was delivering the closing address after the party’s NEC meeting at the weekend. This is developing story    